properties.Name: LeaseType
properties.Description:
The type of commercial lease arrangement.

Ex:
- Percentage Lease
- Net Lease
- Double Net Lease
- Triple Net Lease
- Fully Serviced Lease (Gross Lease)

Where:

Percentage Lease
Base Rent + Percent of Monthly Sales

Net Lease
In additional to rent, tenant pays some or all of taxes, insurance, or maintenance.

Double Net Lease
Tenant pays rent + taxes and insurance.

Triple Net Lease
Tenant pays rent + taxes, insurance, and maintenance.

Fully Serviced Lease (Gross Lease)
Landlord directly pays all or most usual costs. These costs are often passed on to tenant in rent as a "Load Factor."
